about.summary: The objective of this package is to perform inference using an expressive statistical grammar that coheres with the tidy design framework.

name: r-infer
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.5.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-infer
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/infer_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/infer/infer_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 48385a4a222de02db108d422553589879473b1cca4b37013ba235618ce5e4254

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr >=0.7.0
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-glue >=1.3.0
    - r-magrittr
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang >=0.2.0
    - r-tibble
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr >=0.7.0
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-glue >=1.3.0
    - r-magrittr
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang >=0.2.0
    - r-tibble

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('infer')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('infer')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/tidymodels/infer
  license: CC0-1.0
  summary: The objective of this package is to perform inference using an expressive statistical grammar that coheres with the tidy design framework.
  license_family: CC

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
